# Slow Cooker Marry Me Chicken Orzo
https://www.facebook.com/share/r/15dzoPsKUt/

## Macros (Makes 10 Servings) 
Macros Per Serving: 
- 450 Calories
- 50g Protein
- 23g carbs 
- 7g Fat 

## Ingredients: 
- 60oz Chicken Breast (1700g)
- 1 Tbsp Garlic Salt (15g)
- 1 Tbsp Italian Seasoning (7g)
- 1 Tbsp Smoked Paprika (7g)
- 4 Tbsps Tomato Paste (60g)
- 8 Garlic Cloves (25g)
- 3 Cups Dry Orzo (570g)
- 4 Cups Chicken Bone Broth (960g)
- 1 Cup Diced White Onions (150g)
- 1 Cup Sun Dried Tomatoes (50g)
- 2 Cups Blended Cottage Cheese (450g) 
- 1 Cup Parmesan (100g)
- 1 Small Bag of Spinach (200g)
- 3 Tbsps Lemon Juice (45g) 

Additional Notes: To reheat the meal preps from frozen, follow these steps: Add a few tablespoon of water to the container, cover with a wet paper towel, and microwave for around 5-6 minutes


# Instruction
- insert Chicken breasts, seasonings, and garlic cloves into slow cooker, mix and cook on high for 2 hours
-  When chicken is done cooking add in bone broth, dry orzo, diced onions and dried tomatoes. Combine and cook on high for 30 minutes.
- When orzo is soft add in blended cottage cheese, parmesan, fresh spinach and lemon juice